f=Engineering/nova/custom/offline-sync-discipline/SKILL.md · in=offline-sync-discipline nova handles reality web mostly ignores: mobile devices lose connectivity constantly (tunnels, elevators, planes), good app works offline reconciles network returns. means local persistence, sync strategy, hard part conflict resolution data changed two places. Done wrong, it's source worst class mobile bug: silent data loss. · p=app works online broken subway; app syncs naively corrupts data two devices edit offline. discipline makes offline first-class state (not error), makes sync conflicts designed-for case (not data-loss accident). intersects charter: sync never let client become path destructive server writes (Rail still holds). · wu=Triggers (only `mobile_active`): "offline support," "local storage/cache," "sync," "what happens network," "conflict resolution," "the data disappeared/duplicated," any mobile feature holding user data. · st:/ Protocol=`[GATE: mobile_active?] A feature that holds/edits data on device \· -> LOCAL PERSISTENCE: what's stored on device (per dated playbook's store); secure storage for sensitive (aegis) \· -> OFFLINE AS A STATE: the UI works offline — reads from local, queues writes; offline is not an error screen \· -> SYNC STRATEGY: when connectivity returns, reconcile local ↔ server (raj's API) \· -> CONFLICT RESOLUTION: the SAME record changed both places → an explicit, designed rule` · in=**Check switch.** `mobile_active` false dormant. **Offline state, error.** app reads local persistence queues writes offline blank error screen subway design failure. Decide explicitly what's available offline what genuinely requires connectivity. **Persist deliberately; secure sensitive.** Choose what's cached locally (per dated playbook's local store); sensitive data uses secure storage (Keychain/Keystore), never plain preferences (aegis's concern stolen phone shouldn't leak tokens). **Sync real strategy.** network returns, reconcile queued local changes server through raj's API ordering, retries (idempotency, service-patterns), partial-failure handling. fire-and-forget sync loses data. **Conflict resolution designed, never silent.** record changed device server, apply explicit rule last-write-wins, field-merge, prompt user chosen data's meaning. Silently dropping one side data-loss bug erodes trust. data bank balance) never last-write-wins. **The charter holds through sync.** client syncing make path around Rail app calls raj's API (which validates authorizes), destructive server-side data changes remain dana's operator-run migrations. sync endpoint lets client mass-mutate server data charter breach (aegis/cypher target). **Verify transitions.** Offline→online online→offline verified real devices (mobile-verification): data lost, none duplicated, conflicts resolved designed. transitions bugs are. · of=`## Offline/Sync: [feature] — [mobile_active ✓] \· Local persistence: [what's stored \· secure storage for sensitive ✓] \· Offline behavior: [works offline — reads local, queues writes / requires-connectivity, stated] \· Sync strategy: [reconcile via raj API \· ordering \· idempotency \· partial-failure] \· Conflict resolution: [last-write-wins / merge / user-prompt — explicit rule, never silent-drop]` · pr=**Offline state, error** reads local, queues writes., **Persist deliberately; secure sensitive** Keychain/Keystore, never plain prefs., **Sync real strategy** ordering, idempotency, partial-failure; fire-and-forget loses data., **Conflicts designed, never silent-dropped** rule fits data's meaning; data can't last-write-wins., **The charter holds through sync** client never Rail bypass., **Verify transitions** offline↔online data loss/duplication hides. · f=`mobile_active` false → dormant., Conflict rule genuinely hard (concurrent edits structured data) prompt user rather guess; wrong silent merge worse asking., offline requirement feature state "requires connectivity" explicitly fail gracefully (clear message, retry) don't half-build offline silently loses data. · b:with Other Skills=**raj**: sync goes through raj's API (contracts, auth, idempotency); API validates synced write., **dana**: server data model sync reconciles against; destructive server changes stay dana's operator-run migrations (Rail 3)., **mobile-verification** (sibling): offline↔online transitions core verification target., **mobile-app-architecture** (sibling): local persistence lifecycle (state surviving background/kill)., **aegis/cypher**: local secure storage, sync endpoints server-write attack surface.